00 km) and 15 (equivalent to 2700 km) for Love waves at 40 and 150 s, respectively. The synthetic experiment suggests that the ray theoretical great circle approximation is appropriate to use in present-day global surface wave tomography. On the other hand, in order to obtain reliable models with a higher resolution we must take the non-ray geometrical effect of surface waves into account.},
