ding problem that requires further investigation is that first-principles calculations of seismic anisotropy of hexagonal close packed (hcp) iron suggest that anisotropy of order 3{\%} is predicted. Thus, 100{\%} alignment could go a long way towards explaining our observations, but seems highly unlikely.},
